istener callback, with optional error information.\n\nMethod Name Enumeration:\n- ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName in ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName.java: Enumeration providing compile-time assurance for the three callback method names (ON_PARTITIONS_REVOKED, ON_PARTITIONS_ASSIGNED, ON_PARTITIONS_LOST) defined in the ConsumerRebalanceListener interface.\n\nMetrics Management:\n- RebalanceMetricsManager (abstract base class) in metrics/RebalanceMetricsManager.java: Abstract base class defining the interface for rebalance-related metrics recording with methods for tracking rebalance start/end events and failed rebalances.\n- ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager in metrics/ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager.java: Concrete implementation extending RebalanceMetricsManager that manages metrics for consumer group rebalancing, tracking rebalance latency (avg, max, total), rebalance frequency (per hour), and failed rebalance events.\n- ShareRebalanceMetricsManager in metrics/ShareRebalanceMetricsManager.java: Concrete implementation extending RebalanceMetricsManager for Share consumer group rebalancing metrics, tracking rebalance total count and rate per hour.\n- RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager in metrics/RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager.java: Manages metrics specific to rebalance listener callback latencies, tracking average and maximum execution time for partition-revoked, partition-assigned, and partition-lost callbacks."
